Reasoning: The paper deals with randomized query complexity, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also introduces a new complexity measure, the max conflict complexity, which is related to the study of Boolean functions and their properties (cs.DS). The paper also uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) to prove its results. Finally, the paper's focus on composition theorems and lower bounds is also relevant to the field of discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
